JOHANNESBURG - For most 11-year-olds, free time means play time, but that's not the case for Stacey Fru. She spends her free time writing books. At only 11-years-old, Fru has already written eight books, two of which have been published, with a third on the way next month. One of her books has been approved by the Basic Education department as suitable reading for young pupils. The author sat down with eNCA anchor Thulasizwe Simelane to discuss her work. * For more on this story, watch the video in the above. eNCA